==Colloquoial English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /mɛk/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /mEk/

===Noun===
''''''mec'''
''' (''plural'' '''mec''')
"mec" is a nonsensical word used to convey feelings of distaste or frustration, it can also be used in place of swear-words.
For example:
"Mec"
or "That Mec'king bastard"
or "What the Mec are you smoking"

Pronounced: meq
Variations: meck, mech, mek, malsgom

Modifications: If the word is spoken in a long drawn out fashion reminiscint to that of a person on drugs, than it is known as a "waugh-call" as it is used to attracct the attention of a special someone.

Derivation: The term "mec" is a colloquial adaptation of the initals of a fictional army, the Middle Eastern Coalation in the ever popular computer game franchise "Battlefield 2"[http://www.ea.com/official/battlefield/battlefield2/us/home.jsp]